                        <item xml:id="e1">- Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) added in the upper margins of fols.  72v-73r, 77v-78r, 87r-88r, 90v-91r. &#xD;
- Names of the feasts, title of the works indicating the readings are written in the upper margin of some fols.:  &#xD;
ʾit wäybalḥǝkǝmu: fol. 2r&#xD;
mäśärätä kälʿa: fol. 3r&#xD;
mǝnbab zä-ʾǝhud särk, between two lines: fol. 4v&#xD;
hardly readable: fol.118v&#xD;
unreadable: fol.119r&#xD;
Lahǝya dǝngǝl: fol. 124r&#xD;
zä-su&lt;...&gt;: fol. 128r, rubricated. &#xD;
- Names of the feasts, title of the works indicating the readings are crudely written in the upper margin of some fols. by a recent hand: fol. 7v, in pencil; fol. 57v, in blue pen; fol. 99r, in red pen; fol. 104r, in blue pen; fol. 113av, in blue pen; fol. 116r, in blue pen and pencil.&#xD;
- Erasures in fols. 32rc, 108v, 123vc, 133vb, 133vc.&#xD;
- Unfilled spaces left for rubrication in fols. 71vb, 75v (?), 95r and in Additiones 1, 3.&#xD;
- Immediate correction of the text: a passage is framed in fols. 27ra, 134rb, 134vc.&#xD;
- Omitted passage in fol. 26va is added in the empty ruled line by a secondary hand.&#xD;
- Some passages are underlined by blue pen in fols. 88ra, 93rb.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of crosses in fol. 60r; crude drawing of a small cross (?) in fol. 88r. &#xD;
- Thread inserted in fol. 88 for navigating in the text.&#xD;
- Writing excercises in fols. 3v, 4r, 5r.</item>
